JOHANNESBURG &#8211; Moody&#8217;s has warned that South African government drawdowns are rising and represent increasing risks to its fiscal position, a day after Treasury targeted the wealthy with tax hikes in a bid to rein in the budget deficit.Zuzana Brixiova, a lead analyst for South Africa, said the budget aimed to stabilise the debt-to-GDP ratio but &#8220;while government guarantees relative to GDP are also projected to stabilise, their actual drawdowns are rising and represent increasing risks to the government&#8217;s fiscal position.&#8221;